{"content":"<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">After five years of meticulous effort, Italian band Eva Can’t is ready to release their highly anticipated fifth album, “Emisferi” on September 20th. The creation of this album involved four different recording studios and countless hours of rehearsing and refining. “Emisferi” promises to be an extraordinary addition to the progressive and post-metal scene, with a rich and intricate sound that reflects the band's dedication and evolution over the years.</p><p class='lead'><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>Why Give It a Listen? For a Unique Hemispheric Quest!</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">“Emisferi” is structured as a concept album divided into 17 tracks, organized into four distinct parts that take listeners on a sonic journey from pole to pole on an uninhabited planet. The stylistic coordinates of the album traverse genres from post-metal and post rock to moments of progressive and modern black metal. Each section represents a different element, recorded in diverse settings to capture unique auditory textures. The album cover, created by Helios Pu (aka Porz of Malnàtt), complements the album’s epic scope, enhancing the listener’s immersive experience.</p><p class='lead'><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>A Labor of Love</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">Guitarist and vocalist Simone Lanzoni describes “Emisferi” as a zealous project that encapsulates an emotional and physical odyssey.&nbsp;</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><em>“The album is an ambitious work that I hope will leave an indelible mark on all those who listen to it as it has left on us”</em>, says Simone Lanzoni.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">The masterpiece was recorded in various locations, including BRB Studio, Vacuum Studio, Fallout Studio, and an isolated house on the hills of Bologna, each chosen for their ability to contribute a distinct sonic quality. Lanzoni hopes the album will have a lasting impact on its audience.</p>","title":"NEW ALBUM: Eva Can’t Drops “Emisferi” — A Spectacular Quest in Sound","details":"Post / prog / rock / metal band from Italy","Socials":"<p class='lead'><a href='https://www.facebook.com/evacantofficial'><i class='bi bi-facebook'></i></a> <a href='https://www.instagram.com/evacantofficial/'><i class='bi bi-instagram'></i></a> <a href='https://open.spotify.com/artist/02MpaZ7QuyQ0PdqsM6iGmT'><i class='bi bi-spotify'></i></a> <a href='https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCT3ofUZaC04Z6dj0XXFuDmA'><i class='bi bi-youtube'></i></a></p>","img01":"https://pulse-of-the-underground.com/assets/441525811_10225432808742940_248116143813906946_n.jpg","sub":"gbK4OvgKbyYDfYCfIjboOqjA9Yv1","date":"29/05/2024","lang":"en","translations":{"en":"NEW-ALBUM-Eva-Cant-Drops-Emisferi--An-Epic-Journey-in-Sound.json","el":"ΝΕΟΑΛΜΠΟΥΜ-ΟιEvaCan-tΚυκλοφορούντο-Emisferi--μιαΜοναδικήΗμισφαιρικήΑναζήτηση--el.json"},"isReady":true,"category":"Latest Reviews(ENG)"}